I merged this up this morning, but the notification part of the Apache infrastructure seems to not be working this morning.

Yes,  I was trying to combine mxudr and SQL executor JVM startup to one. In case of SQL executor JVM startup parameter is purely environment variable driven. But in case of udr it is both CQD (control query default) and environment variable driven. Hence it become difficult to combine.  TM code is merely a clone of SQL executor code with subtle differences to sync it with their respective components.
Is this a requirement from Apache? Changing the package name would mean the existing application needs to be updated to load the new driver isn't?

I think there are 2 other issues with this change.  I think the directory of the java programs needs to be in sync with package name for use in eclipse and other IDEs.  @zellerh can confirm this.  In addition, I didn't see the corresponding change in trafci. I wonder if trafci is broken with this change

I am not clear on the need to change the package name. If so, I think the directory of the java programs needs to be in sync with package name for use in eclipse and other IDEs. @zellerh can confirm this

Sorry, can't confirm for sure, as I have not tried that, but here is what I believe (not know).
My hope was that we could just change the group id in Maven to org.apache.trafodion.x and leave the package name unchanged, org.trafodion.x. My assumption is that Maven does not insist that the group id matches all the classes inside the artifact.

It looks like you already went ahead and changed the package names. In that case I agree with Selva, we should then also change the directories. I'm surprised that Maven would build with a mismatch between directory names and package names (or is this built with a Makefile?). If you do this move, make sure to do it with git mv, so that git knows the files have been moved and aren't new. Otherwise you may cause a lot of merge conflicts or lose changes.
@zellerh the directory has been changed. Yes, if the directory does not change, maven can also work fine. To keep consistent, it has been changed. For git mv, yes, as you see, already applied.

The impact of changing the package name in Type2 driver is confined to the server applications running on the Trafodion cluster.  However, please consider sending a notice to dev and user list about this upcoming change
@arvind-narain Is this PR active still? If no, can you please close this PR
